& [SlotMappingTable] is the current comparison
  + [row_001_tail_to_p_h] is source tail module as harmonic pressure p_h
    = mapping_status: not_admitted
    = reason: source tail is described as far-field and cutoff debris, while p_h is the harmonic correction tied to the local pressure projection frame
    = missing_feature: source text must identify a harmonic pressure component or harmonic correction estimate
  + [row_002_tail_to_p_0] is source tail module as local pressure p_0 generated by Navier-Stokes tensor/source terms
    = mapping_status: plausible_partial
    = reason: p_0 is associated with forcing or tensor terms such as u tensor u and gradient contributions, so cutoff/source debris could plausibly enter here
    = missing_feature: formula-level rewrite of the source tail as a projected tensor/source contribution
  + [row_003_tail_to_projection_remainder] is source tail module as nonlocal or outer-pressure projection remainder
    = mapping_status: plausible_partial
    = reason: source table names far-field debris, which is closest to nonlocal/outer-pressure remainder language
    = missing_feature: projection estimate connecting far-field tail to a larger-scale velocity or pressure norm
  + [row_004_tail_to_cutoff_error] is source tail module as cutoff/localization error term
    = mapping_status: plausible_partial
    = reason: source tail also bundles cutoff debris, which should be separated from pressure-size smallness
    = missing_feature: cutoff error bound preserving the epsilon threshold

& [MappingReading] is the developed obstruction
  + [mapping_result] is partial_ambiguous_mapping
  + [not_p_h] is the source tail should not be assigned to harmonic pressure without explicit harmonic source text
  + [likely_slots] is p_0_or_projection_remainder_or_cutoff_error
  + [first_lock] is source tail bundles multiple slots and must be split before any projection estimate can be applied
  + [second_lock] is no larger-scale velocity or pressure norm controls the far-field part yet
  + [third_lock] is cutoff debris has no threshold-preserving absorption estimate
  + [proof_promotion_status] is blocked
  + [lock_mass_change] is none

& [NextBoundedMotion] is the follow-up
